      "content": "That's a pretty strong stance. You mentioned that regulation is the \"only viable path,\" but isn't that a bit of an exaggeration? A lot of people in the industry say that the \"existential risk\" stuff is mostly science fiction used to justify monopolies. Can you explain why you're framing it as a settled necessity rather than a speculative debate?",
